---
Manage persisted REPL history

- Usage ----------------------------------------------------------------
  osp history [OPTIONS] <COMMAND>

- Commands -------------------------------------------------------------
  list   List persisted history entries
  prune  Retain only the newest `keep` entries
  clear  Remove all persisted history entries
  help   Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

- Options --------------------------------------------------------------
  -i, --incognito
          Disable persistent REPL history and other identity-linked behavior
      --profile <PROFILE>
          Select the active config profile for the invocation
      --no-env
          Skip environment-derived config sources
      --no-config-file
          Skip config-file-derived sources
      --defaults-only
          Use only built-in defaults and explicit in-memory overrides.
          This is stricter than combining `--no-env` and `--no-config-file`: it also disables env/path bootstrap discovery through `HOME`, `XDG_*`, `OSP_CONFIG_FILE`, and `OSP_SECRETS_FILE`.
      --plugin-dir <PLUGIN_DIRS>
          Add one or more plugin discovery directories
      --theme <THEME>
          Override the selected output theme
      --presentation <PRESENTATION>
          [possible values: expressive, compact, austere]
      --gammel-og-bitter
  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

- Common Invocation Options --------------------------------------------
  --format <auto|guide|json|table|mreg|value|md>
                                            Format this invocation only
  --guide | --json | --table | --mreg | --value | --md
                                            Convenience aliases for --format
  --mode <auto|plain|rich>                  Render mode for this invocation
  --plain | --rich                          Convenience aliases for --mode
  --color <auto|always|never>               Color policy for this invocation
  --unicode <auto|always|never>             Unicode policy for this invocation
  --ascii                                   Alias for --unicode never
  -v, --verbose                             Increase message verbosity
  -q, --quiet                               Decrease message verbosity
  -d, --debug                               Increase developer log verbosity
  --cache                                   Reuse identical result in this REPL session
  --plugin-provider <PLUGIN_ID>             Select provider for this invocation
These flags may appear anywhere before `--` and affect only the current command.
`--cache` is available only inside the interactive REPL.
------------------------------------------------------------------------
